# Pull requests — wait for CI

When you create or update a pull request (`gh pr create`, push to a PR branch):

1. After push, poll CI with `gh pr checks` or `gh run list` / `gh run watch` until workflows finish (do not stop at "PR opened").
2. If any required check fails, investigate (`gh run view`, logs), fix on the branch, push again, and re-wait until green.
3. Only report the PR as done when required checks are successful (or clearly explain blockers the user must resolve, e.g. missing secrets).

Do not treat "PR created" as complete while CI is still running or red.
